    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is the scan painful?",
        "answer": "No. You’ll feel nothing except the table moving.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How long does it take?",
        "answer": "15–30 minutes in the machine; allow 60 minutes total for paperwork and positioning.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I drive home afterwards?",
        "answer": "Absolutely—no sedatives or contrast mean you’re road-ready instantly.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will I get my report?",
        "answer": "Same day for scans before 3 p.m.; next morning for late slots.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I’m claustrophobic?",
        "answer": "Choose our open MRI or request mild sedation with prior consultation.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What should I wear for my MRI Hip Without Contrast scan?",
        "answer": "When **preparing for MRI hip without contrast**, wear comfortable, loose-fitting clothes that do not have any metal parts (zippers, snaps, buckles, underwires in bras, metallic threads). You will most likely be asked to change into a medical gown provided by Cadabams Diagnostics to ensure there is no metal interference with the scan and for your safety."
      }
